[{"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Microsoft is now giving many Surface PCs at least six years of firmware updates", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Surface Laptop Studio 2 in tent mode, displaying Windows 11.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/fp2RRRtCByD9fDbRKcO-VwlUo_g=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72827056/236818_Surface_Laptop_Studio_2_AKrales_0061.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"K72qrI\">Microsoft Surface PCs that have shipped on or after January 1st, 2021 will get at least six years of driver and firmware updates, according to <a href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/surface/surface-driver-firmware-lifecycle-support\">a Microsoft support document</a> reported on <a href=\"https://www.windowscentral.com/hardware/surface/microsoft-commits-to-6-years-of-firmware-updates-for-new-surface-pcs-going-forward\">by <em>Windows Central</em></a>. Previously, Microsoft had only said it would support devices with at least four years of those updates from when they first came out, as you can se", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/3/23945728/microsoft-surface-pc-six-years-firmware-updates-support", "date_published": "2023-11-03T22:24:42+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Microsoft employees will keep free access to Xbox Game Pass Ultimate after complaints", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Xbox Game Pass gift cards\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/02nd16iJ-e5ZFlgcJEf_Ol7iDXc=/0x0:4232x2821/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72826983/1234934021.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Beata Zawrzel/NurPhoto via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"STp73H\">Microsoft was planning to remove a free Xbox Game Pass Ultimate benefit for most of its 238,000 employees in January, but the company is now reversing that decision following employee complaints. <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/2/23944124/microsoft-xbox-game-pass-ultimate-free-employee-removed\"><em>The Verge </em>reported yesterday</a> that Microsoft employees had expressed objections about the Xbox Game Pass Ultimate benefit being removed in 2024, with Xbox chief Phil Spencer personally looking into the situation.</p>\n<p id=\"2izWzn\">Spencer has now confirmed that the decision will be reversed and that Microsoft employees will keep the Xbox Game Pass Ult", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/3/23945294/microsoft-xbox-game-pass-ultimate-free-employee-perk-restored", "date_published": "2023-11-03T22:02:50+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "In a first, Marvel\u2019s Echo is coming to both Disney Plus and Hulu at the same time", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image of Alaqua Cox as Maya Lopez. She\u2019s dressed in combat gear and sitting on machinery looking exhausted after a fight.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1TPx73KR7Kneeoq13sFy8x-YNvA=/0x0:5472x3648/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72826003/GRH_4T4A0362_R2.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Marvel Studios / Chuck Zlotnick</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"zsW3ge\">Alaqua Cox\u2019s Maya Lopez <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/12/22/22849870/hawkeye-season-1-review-disney-plus\">immediately stood out</a> when she appeared in Disney Plus\u2019 <em>Hawkeye</em> back in 2021. Among a cast of charismatic goofballs and assassins with hearts of gold, Maya was a terrifyingly deadly foil, constantly reminding the audience and characters of the stakes. Disney was so enamored with Cox\u2019s portrayal of the deaf Native American heroine, it <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/17/23096167/marvel-echo-series-disney-plus-2023-first-image\">greenlit a", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/3/23945203/marvel-echo-disney-plus-hulu-dual-release-date", "date_published": "2023-11-03T18:01:11+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Google scraps $15 billion deal with lead developer of Silicon Valley campus projects", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A mixed use space with people milling about the greens, next to office buildings and the San Jose Water Company\u2019s historic building.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Spuo_78_R_D-FvvtJ8aGexQ8eJ4=/80x0:944x576/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72825896/fVqGMEj8Yvvajhj6SqHF9HKKIraBP_VI.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>A render of the proposed San Jose development.</em> | Image: Google</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"LqGrgI\">Google has ended its agreement with Lendlease, the lead developer it had been working with on four major campus projects in Silicon Valley. In an <a href=\"https://www.lendlease.com/siteassets/lendlease/shared/investor-centre/announcements/asx/2023/11/2635882.pdf\">announcement published earlier on Friday</a>, Lendlease said both companies had agreed to end the deal after determining that \u201cthe existing agreements are no longer mutually beneficial given current market conditions.\u201d </p>\n<p id=\"Y50hbh\">The deal covered", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/3/23945098/google-lendlease-silicon-valley-campus-development-deal-end-housing", "date_published": "2023-11-03T17:44:10+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Microsoft\u2019s fullscreen\u00a0Xbox\u00a0pop-up ads don\u2019t have to be annoying", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A pop-up ad on Xbox for Call of Duty: Modern Warfare III\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NrkTZmCectE16bkgtqEKEvVwEYM=/0x0:2560x1707/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72825830/codad.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Screenshot by Tom Warren / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"9gFQv6\">When I turned my Xbox on yesterday, I was greeted with a fullscreen pop-up ad for <em>Call of Duty: Modern Warfare III</em>. I posted on X (Twitter) about it and thought nothing more of it because annoying as it was, this isn\u2019t the first time Microsoft has used a fullscreen takeover to promote one of its new games \u2014 and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/13/23791235/microsoft-activision-blizzard-acquisition-complete-finalized\">Microsoft now owns <em>Call of Duty</em></a>.</p>\n<p id=\"rvnL0n\">But the internet wasn\u2019t happy about this particular one. \u201cIs this what we should expect now that Xbox owns <em>Call of Duty</em>?\u201d asked <a href=\"https:/", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/3/23945174/microsoft-xbox-fullscreen-pop-up-ad-call-of-duty-modern-warfare-3-xbox-consoles", "date_published": "2023-11-03T17:30:20+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "BlizzCon 2023: all the latest news and trailers", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"BlizzCon 2017\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5APF2WRXHeTSSNX4DfAHkumGYP0=/0x0:5198x3465/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72825713/869916976.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Joe Scarnici / Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>Stay up to date on the biggest announcements from the developer behind Overwatch, Diablo, and World of Warcraft.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/3/23944811/blizzcon-2023-news-trailers-diablo-warcraft-overwatch\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/3/23944811/blizzcon-2023-news-trailers-diablo-warcraft-overwatch", "date_published": "2023-11-03T17:05:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The Verge\u2019s 2023 PC gift guide", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of hands holding various products against a brightly colored graphic background of stars.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NKp7YtAgU_mcPIzB9I2SJBfnyLU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72825088/236830_PC_Gift_Guide_Art_CVirginia_LEDE_2040x1360.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo Illustration by Amelia Holowaty Krales and Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The best tech gifts for those who spend way too much time sitting at a laptop or desktop PC \u2014 whether for work or leisure.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23919557/holiday-gift-ideas-2023-pc-desktop-laptop-wfh-content-creator-tech-gadgets\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23919557/holiday-gift-ideas-2023-pc-desktop-laptop-wfh-content-creator-tech-gadgets", "date_published": "2023-11-03T15:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "This little tool can crash an iPhone running iOS 17", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image of a Flipper Zero over a red and black swirl illustration\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TIG7oMQV_v3ed_Z-77f7asHKDCA=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72825068/226349_Flipper.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Lille Allen / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"UWAwFR\">Security researchers have discovered that iPhones updated to iOS 17 are susceptible to a Bluetooth attack using a Flipper Zero device that can crash the phone. <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/security/2023/11/flipper-zero-gadget-that-doses-iphones-takes-once-esoteric-attacks-mainstream/\"><em>Ars Technica </em>reports</a> that security researcher <a href=\"https://infosec.exchange/@1sand0s/111254888425599114\">Jeroen van der Ham</a> fell victim to the exploit on a train journey last month, with his phone displaying multiple pop-up windows before rebooting.</p>\n<p id=\"7mIEM0\">Van der Ham discovered that the attacker, another pass", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/3/23944901/apple-iphone-ios-17-flipper-zero-attack-bluetooth", "date_published": "2023-11-03T14:56:19+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Soon you\u2019ll be able to safely microwave Cup Noodles (you weren\u2019t doing that, right?)", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Render of Nissin\u2019s microwavable Cup Noodles packaging.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/gJpyjBOUuG_SRxcv-lIMySeYYc8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72825005/Nissin_Foods_70662_03003_Cup_Noodles_Chicken_Unit_JPEG.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Nissin\u2019s microwavable Cup Noodles will hit shelves in 2024.</em> | Image: Nissin Foods</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"rH8H1B\">Last week, Nissin announced that it was updating the design of its iconic Cup Noodles in early 2024. Instead of polystyrene, it\u2019ll be made out of paper. Nissin also notes that thanks to the new packaging, its Cup Noodles will now be microwaveable. As in, you were never supposed to be microwaving Cup Noodles. </p>\n<p id=\"1qt8tH\">Cue chaos.</p>\n<p id=\"LBPMyO\">As it turns out, many people have not been reading labels when heating up Cup Noodles \u2014 a staple of college dorms, kitchen pantries, and many childhood memories. On social media, several people <", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/3/23944815/nissin-cup-noodles-microwave-2024", "date_published": "2023-11-03T14:39:49+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The new Echo Show 5 and Apple\u2019s leather AirTag Loops are over half off", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The third-gen Echo Show 5 turned on while on a desk in front of the window during a rainy day.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3_uudBsXt77bGH7Dbc3fjV2hzjE=/414x0:2034x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72824964/Echo_Show_5_Shot_3.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>You can get a free smart bulb when you buy the third-gen Echo Show 5 at its all-time low price.</em> | Image: Amazon</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"g3IMC2\">Believe it or not, Amazon\u2019s Alexa is turning eight years old on November 6th, and to celebrate, Amazon is discounting <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/b?node=11851273011&amp;ref_=ods_gw_xpl_AB23\">a number of Alexa-enabled devices</a>. There are a lot of good deals on everything from <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/deal/a01650d1\">streaming sticks</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Introducing-Amazon-Soundbar-speaker-Virtual/dp/B0C4BZ28PG?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">sound", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/3/23944095/amazon-echo-show-5-apple-leather-airtag-loops-lg-g3-oled-tv-deal-sale", "date_published": "2023-11-03T14:27:58+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Fortnite\u2019s new season is a trip through the game\u2019s history", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Art for the Fortnite OG season of Fortnite.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9M7X3ef6pebZhWAkGuLjgewp7yI=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72824473/Fortnite_OG_Key_Art_EN.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Epic Games</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"10EJUc\">The <em>Fortnite</em> island is changing once again \u2014 but this time, it\u2019ll look very familiar to longtime fans. The game just launched its latest season, which has been dubbed \u201c<em>Fortnite</em> OG.\u201d According to developer Epic Games, the game will be regularly updated throughout the season, and \u201ceach major update will bring a different phase of battle royale\u2019s past.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"RaLlHJ\">To start, <em>Fortnite</em> OG will be focused on Chapter 1: Season 5. That means <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/2/23943552/lets-get-tilted\">the return of Tilted Towers</a> (<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/5/4/18529463/fortnite-unvaulting-volcano-eruption-tilte", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/3/23943701/fortnite-og-new-season-tilted-towers-baller", "date_published": "2023-11-03T12:04:36+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Call of Duty can now take up over 200GB of space, but it\u2019s complicated", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot taken from Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 3\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/IdUUcW8wgOJetbqdejU7fussuos=/483x0:3357x1916/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72824339/MW3_CP_REVEAL_08_BRANDED.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>You might need to make space on your hard drive or SSD for to keep all your Call of Duty titles installed.</em> | Image: Activision</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"vqvzP6\">Ahead of the release of <em>Call of Duty: Modern Warfare III</em> on November 10th, Activision has preemptively provided more details about the enormous file size of the game to explain why it\u2019s \u201clarger than last year.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"QLezYJ\"><a href=\"https://www.ign.com/articles/activision-explains-huge-call-of-duty-modern-warfare-3-file-sizes\">As reported by <em>IGN</em></a>, players with early access to the game\u2019s single-player campaign found that the total file size for <em>Call of Duty</em> at installation \u2014 which also includes the", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/3/23944733/call-of-duty-modern-warfare-3-storage", "date_published": "2023-11-03T11:21:31+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Dell put fast 120Hz panels in its latest UltraSharp monitors", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Laptop and desktop plugged into same monitor.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ubjfrfKOHjO6575eFxyEbFr4rh4=/0x0:4219x2813/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72824249/ultrasharp_u2724de_pdp_kvm_connectivity_lifestyle.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Dell\u2019s 27-inch UltraSharp U2724DE.</em> | Image: Dell</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"S5SwpM\">Dell has announced four new UltraSharp monitors that have the potential to be good gaming displays in addition to playing to the brand\u2019s traditional strength of offering color-accurate screens for work. The two 27 inchers have 1440p resolutions, while the other two 24-inch monitors are 1080p. All of them have IPS LCD displays with 120Hz refresh rates, double the 60Hz that Dell has typically offered with its UltraSharp models. </p>\n<p id=\"KoftBA\">While 120Hz monitors have traditionally been of most interest to gamers, who arguably have the most to gain from a screen that updates twice as quickly ", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/3/23944722/dell-ultrasharp-u2424h-u2424he-u2724d-u2724de-120hz-price-release-date-specs-features", "date_published": "2023-11-03T10:52:11+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Sam Bankman-Fried gambled on a trial and his parents lost", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"FTX Co-Founder Sam Bankman-Fried On Trial For Fraud\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/FhbzqDZClWY1tGfZG6RNGjjsO2M=/0x0:7653x5102/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72823584/1748659225.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Over five weeks, the FTX founder\u2019s parents watched from the galleys \u2014 deluded, humiliated, and finally defeated.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/2/23944485/sam-bankman-fried-guilty-verdict-parents\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/2/23944485/sam-bankman-fried-guilty-verdict-parents", "date_published": "2023-11-03T02:34:28+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}]